{"id":320992,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wakasa_Province","text":"was an old province of Japan in the area of Fukui Prefecture on the island of Honsh\u016B. It was also known as or.\nThe province had borders with Echizen, \u014Cmi, Tamba, Tango, and Yamashiro Provinces.\nThe ancient capital city of the province was Obama.\nHistory.\nIn the Meiji period, the provinces of Japan were converted into prefectures. The maps of Japan and Wakasa Province were reformed in the 1870s.\nShrines and Temples.\n\"Wakasahiko jinja\" was the chief Shinto shrine (\"ichinomiya\") of Wakasa.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"List_of_Provinces_of_Japan","surface_form":"old province","offset":7},{"uri":"Japan","surface_form":"Japan","offset":23},{"uri":"Fukui_Prefecture","surface_form":"Fukui Prefecture","offset":44},{"uri":"Honsh%C5%AB","surface_form":"Honsh\u016B","offset":78},{"uri":"Border","surface_form":"border","offset":128},{"uri":"Echizen_Province","surface_form":"Echizen","offset":141},{"uri":"%C5%8Cmi_Province","surface_form":"\u014Cmi","offset":150},{"uri":"Tamba_Province","surface_form":"Tamba","offset":155},{"uri":"Tango_Province","surface_form":"Tango","offset":162},{"uri":"Yamashiro_Province","surface_form":"Yamashiro","offset":173},{"uri":"Capital_(city)","surface_form":"capital city","offset":206},{"uri":"Obama%2C_Fukui","surface_form":"Obama","offset":239},{"uri":"Meiji_period","surface_form":"Meiji period","offset":262},{"uri":"Reform","surface_form":"reform","offset":375},{"uri":"Wakasahiko_jinja","surface_form":"Wakasahiko jinja","offset":420},{"uri":"Shinto_shrine","surface_form":"Shinto shrine","offset":452},{"uri":"Ichinomiya","surface_form":"ichinomiya","offset":468}]}